@tristaZero @roodkcab I think I have to say -1 for this PR. It is not a right way to use the internal transaction handler to process the XA operations. And it could be a risk on data consistent especially when the crash recovery happens. As I mentioned before, the ```SetAutoCommit``` handler which starts a ```BEGIN``` looks like very weird. 

@roodkcab can you just remove the following line and I think all of XA related statments should be passed broadcast to the backend databases to see if it works.
https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/blob/bfb784c9a0e47fd147c8a654c2f0b2a1e86c2c27/shardingsphere-proxy/shardingsphere-proxy-backend/src/main/java/org/apache/shardingsphere/proxy/backend/text/transaction/TransactionBackendHandlerFactory.java#L61

Thanks in advance !

Oh, I get a little bit further investigation. And I found that ```SetAutoCommit``` is a beginning  of a local transaction that shardingsphere is used to mark the current connection is ```inTransaction``` since ```java.sql.Connection``` does not have a ```begin()``` method.

if transaction type is ```LOCAL```, localTransactionManger just to call ```setAutoCommit(false)``` in all backend databases in ```begin()``` method. And if transaction type is not ```LOCAL``` and shardingTransactionManager is set. The ```shardingTransactionManager.begin()``` will be invoked. I think understand the logic of ```SetAutoCommit``` here, is it right ? @terrymanu 

So I think we have to process the ```xa_start``` with
```
if (connection.isInTransaction()) {
    commit(); // commit a transaction in current connection
}

connection.setInXA(true); // set current connection in XA mode
broadcast(); // pass the xa_start to all of the backend database
```

in ```xa_commit``` and ```xa_rollback```
```
connection.setInXA(false);
broadcast(); 
```
And in all of other local transaction operations the following check should be applied
```
if (connection.isInXA()) {
    throw RuntimeException("There is a pending XA transaction !");
}
```

